UID:6hasrhtegi3446quu55ccgkh3a@google.com
CREATED:20181130T003738Z
DESCRIPTION:Now or Ever: Pursuing Justice in an Unjust World Fri | 1/11 | P
 eninsula Temple Beth El | 7:45 pm Do we act with urgency and immediacy or w
 ork toward longer term\, more strategic solutions? We’ll explore a tension 
 between two perhaps contradictory spiritual and moral imperatives—rooted in
  the Talmud and the teachings of Dr. King—of critical importance to us as J
 ews and human beings in the world in this moment: the fierce urgency of now
 \, and the fact that the arc of the moral universe\, though it bends toward
  justice\, is long.
LAST-MODIFIED:20190108T225444Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:PJCC SIR Lecture - Sanctuary
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
