CREATED:20130710T212644Z
DESCRIPTION:Come and honor Sylvia Aftel on the occasion of her 103rd birthd
 ay!  Members of the Beth El Senior Friendship club will enjoy a buffet deli
  luncheon catered by Max’s.  Members must RSVP by Nov. 26.  Call Rhonda Pre
 ss at 378-2717 to reserve your place. Following lunch\, there will be a mus
 ical program with autoharpist\, singer and historian\, Adam Miller. The pro
 gram “Folksongs of Abraham Lincoln and the War Between the States" features
  songs of the era. It is fun to learn history through music.
